## Decisions and Action Items

### Decisions
1. **Feature Preservation in `draft-ietf-bfd-rfc5882-bis`**: Features like *Admin Down* and *Graceful Restart* will remain in the Full Standard because multiple vendor implementations support them, despite not being supported in the ZTE implementation.
2. **Author List Merging**: The author lists of RFC 5884 and RFC 7726 will be merged in `draft-ietf-bfd-rfc5884-bis`. The chairs will request a waiver of the 5-author limit from the IESG during review.

### Action Items
* **All Implementers**: Submit implementation status reports for [draft-ietf-bfd-rfc5880bis](https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/draft-ietf-bfd-rfc5880bis/) and [draft-ietf-bfd-rfc5881bis](https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/draft-ietf-bfd-rfc5881bis/) as soon as possible.
* **Prasad Miriyala**: Audit major implementations regarding the handling of remote BFD discriminators in LSP Echo replies versus control packets to resolve the issue raised by Greg Mirsky in [draft-ietf-bfd-rfc5884-bis](https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/draft-ietf-bfd-rfc5884-bis/).
* **Xiao Min**: Update [draft-ietf-bfd-rfc5883-bis](https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/draft-ietf-bfd-rfc5883-bis/) with the consensus wording on the multi-hop Echo restriction, retaining the "in other words" clarifying clause.

